description:
&lt;p&gt;Would you like to work in the community? Do you want a new challenge?  Come and join our Integrated Care Team –Therapy. We have full and part time vacancies for Senior Therapy Assistant to work in the community based across the city. The Team treats people referred from the Hospital, GPs, District Nurses, and other Health and Social Care teams. We treat adults ranging from the age of 16 upwards with a variety of conditions and therapy needs in their own home environment, working on maintaining and improving independent living. We currently have vacancies in the North, South . East and West  of the city.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a Senior Therapy Assistant, you will work with qualified Physiotherapists and Occupational Therapists and will carry your own patient caseload. You will be supported within the team and will have regular training and supervision.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful applicant should have extensive and relevant experience of working in rehabilitation, have NVQ III in Diagnostic and Therapeutic Care or Health and Social Care (with therapy specific units) or equivalent qualifications or experience.  The applicant must have daily access to a car and have a valid driving license.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a seven day service and covers weekends and Bank Holidays (and late shifts of 10-6). Full and Part time post available 22.5 - 37.5 hours a week. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;


